r his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705207,"age":10,"year":"1585","julianDay":2299970,"title":"The First English Colony is Established in America","description":"England established its first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705208,"age":12,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705212,"age":45,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705213,"age":67,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Elizabeth Sydenham was born before 1575, in London, England. She had at least 1 son with Caleb Cockcroft. She died on 1 March 1680, in her hometown."},"et":{"before 1575–1 March 1680":"enne 1575–1. märts 1680","1570–1645":"1570–1645","1590–1630":"1590–1630","1575–1680":"1575–1680","before 1575":"enne 1575","1680":"1680","1570":"1570","1590":"1590","1645":"1645","1 March 1680":"1. märts 1680","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1630":"1630","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","London, London, England":"London, Sumner, Kansas, Ameerika Ühendriigid","West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Cleveland, Yorkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","London, England":"London, England"},"fi":{"before 1575–1 March 1680":"ennen vuotta 1575–1. maaliskuuta 1680","1570–1645":"1570–1645","1590–1630":"1590–1630","1575–1680":"1575–1680","before 1575":"ennen vuotta 1575","1680":"1680","1570":"1570","1590":"1590","1645":"1645","1 March 1680":"1. maaliskuuta 1680","1642":"1642","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1630":"1630","1575":"1575","1651":"1651","1585":"1585","London, London, England":"London, Sumner, Kansas, Yhdysvallat","West Riding, Yorkshire, England":"Cleveland, Yorkshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kun